29:05.804 --> 29:08.367
operated through the chief. And I well remember 
the first speech I made. My commanding general

29:11.691 --> 29:15.135
told me to go down there and look at the laws. They 
were in existence, change any of them by direction

29:16.313 --> 29:30.370
to suit the job, get on with the war so that the 
natives could cooperate, so our Marines could go

29:16.313 --> 29:30.370
on in training instead of unloading ships. And so 
the Navy was sitting down there expecting to build

29:31.631 --> 29:39.300
a Navy base, which never happened, and they never 
unloaded any ships. So the idea was to get us there,

29:43.060 --> 29:53.072
get the natives to do the work, work unloading 
ships, work on the roads, and do things so that

29:43.060 --> 29:53.072
Marines and other people could be released and get 
on with the training. Didn't they do the work? All

29:55.215 --> 29:58.099
this stuff, these are the annual reports. Did the 
Samoans do the work? The Samoans did their work.

30:01.222 --> 30:07.410
They never had anybody's bad eye on them because 
the Navy had what they called a feeder-feeder

30:01.222 --> 30:07.410
guard there. And through that feeder-feeder 
guard, which was formed in 1904, They lived, the

30:12.608 --> 30:15.091
whole island. They didn't have to work. They just 
sat down and fished and grow taro and this, that,

30:16.152 --> 30:20.517
and the other. They didn't have to do any work. They 
didn't have to work. The sea was full of fish.

30:32.030 --> 30:35.374
So how'd you get them to take over these new duties 
now? I'm sure I'll tell you in a minute.

31:28.445 --> 31:39.196
So on my way back from brigade headquarters, I 
stopped at my military police headquarters to

31:28.445 --> 31:39.196
announce them that I was their new provost 
marshal. I was at Utilee, so I had an office down

31:39.216 --> 31:42.119
there, too.

31:45.583 --> 31:46.884
Feet of field guard, you can have that. Those are 
the people whose salaries filtered through every

31:48.726 --> 31:56.494
native community and family on the island. 
Feeder, feeder, put it on back there. Feeder,

