feeder, go. F-I-T-E, F-I-T-E. All right.

32:08.431 --> 32:09.454
Here, you can have this.

32:33.970 --> 32:38.334
How'd you get the people to take over work? So when I 
reported, I was immediately assigned a jeep.

32:44.039 --> 32:45.621
The Attorney General had a station wagon. I said, I 
didn't want that.

33:00.174 --> 33:03.117
I went down to this office of the Attorney General. 
And the first person I saw was a barefooted Samoan

33:04.987 --> 33:16.601
with a shark lay around his neck, barefooted and a 
lava lava. So I said to him, what's your job? He

33:19.084 --> 33:20.826
says, I'm your chief of police. My name is Paley. 
Paley means strong in Samoan. So I said to him, I am

33:27.174 --> 33:30.758
the attorney general. I'm your lawyer, Celia 
Celia, and I'm the provost of Marquis Island. And I

33:37.828 --> 33:42.976
understand by reading that we have chiefs in the 
different districts. And I want those chiefs to

33:44.378 --> 33:53.652
have as many people of their villages in this 
courtroom tomorrow morning.

33:56.977 --> 34:00.002
So as Bush telegraphed word from one to the other, 
The next morning, the courtroom was filled up, and

34:00.488 --> 34:05.535
I got up and made them a speech. And I told them I 
didn't ask for this duty. But the war was on, and we

34:09.721 --> 34:19.816
had to reorganize and disrupt their easy life 
where they could sleep all day and fish when they

34:09.721 --> 34:19.816
wanted to and grow breadfruit. And now the women do 
all the washing, and they said we had to go to work.

34:24.402 --> 34:25.744
We had to protect this country. If they want to do a 
part, in this Japanese war so they could win it.

34:31.377 --> 34:36.286
They'd have to change their lives, which I 
apologize very much for disrupting it. And we have

34:37.208 --> 34:38.671
to change things. Everybody's gonna work on this 
island. Everybody's gonna produce. We're gonna

34:42.599 --> 34:44.062
set up a labor board. Those who are physically 
qualified are gonna have to work on the roads

34:50.168 --> 34:51.729
You're going to have to keep up your own 
plantation. You're going to have to cut off the

34:51.749 --> 34:53.971
food supply. We cannot be bringing food down from 
the United States for you people when you can grow

34:54.392 --> 34:58.655
it here yourself. We're going to cut off a lot of 
other supplies, shoes and things and other that

34:59.096 --> 35:06.742
you get out of San Francisco. We're going to have to 
cut that off the, you know what I'm talking about,

35:06.863 --> 35:11.046
the list. And we're going to bring down warm 
material. We're going to bring down concrete.

35:16.391 --> 35:20.074
We're going to bring down materials, cement, and 
other materials to win the war with. And you're

35:23.595 --> 35:25.618
going to have to learn to live what you've got. And 
I'm going to only let necessities come to this

35:27.019 --> 35:30.965
island. What'd they say? They didn't say 
anything. I told them that was it. So I got through

35:35.911 --> 35:37.293
talking to them. The next morning, we had all the 
natives that could be physically able to work, all

35:37.313 --> 35:44.943
the men, report for physical examination. And the 
next morning, they went to work. We had trucks go

35:47.006 --> 35:49.369
out into the areas and pick them up. And we taught 
them how to unload ship. We taught them how to be a

35:51.860 --> 35:53.301
winchman. We taught them how to do this, how to drop 
the slings in the hole and all like that. I

35:58.568 --> 36:01.932
cooperated with the supply officer, who was a Navy 
man. I also issued an order immediately that

36:02.713 --> 36:11.683
instead of having one sling down in the hole and 
unload the ship, we're going to have four slings.

36:12.745 --> 36:19.693
And as the law officer of the island aboard ship, 
they had four rules. No stealing, no sleeping, no,

36:20.011 --> 36:41.975
let's see, sleeping, stealing,

36:20.011 --> 36:41.975
drinking, and I had one else. So we set to work, and 
first thing you know, these people went to work

36:43.156 --> 36:48.702
seriously about it. And we used the feet of feet of 
guards as guards on these ships. Everybody that

36:52.984 --> 36:54.866
came on there had to have a ticket. No sleeping, no 
smoking, no stealing. It was another asshole. I

36:58.990 --> 36:59.571
forget what it was. But anyhow, at any time anybody 
violated that, the feet of feet of guards brought

36:59.591 --> 37:06.278
him in, and I would prosecute him. And rather than 
put him in jail, I'd fine him. And I built up

37:09.601 --> 37:15.087
$300,000 or $30,000 in the hospital fund on those 
fines. Anyhow, I could hold court any time. The

37:17.791 --> 37:23.383
court consisted of one naval lieutenant 
commander and three native judges. We had no jury,

37:24.566 --> 37:29.357
so I'd write out the complaint. They'd come in and 
give me the complaint. I'd write it out. If there

37:32.885 --> 37:35.490
was any merit to it, I'd go on and prosecute. If it 
wasn't, I'd give them a warning and go on about

37:35.510 --> 37:37.555
their business. As I say, I gave you all the duties. 
I had the power of adoption. And I found out then

37:43.733 --> 37:51.225
that those natives had more sense than we do 
because they'd bring in a family who had eight

37:43.733 --> 37:51.225
children. They wouldn't adopt just one child. 
They'd adopt every other child so the kids could be

37:53.709 --> 37:56.894
raised together. Those were natives. Anyhow, my 
citation there, I won't. I did a job there, and I was

38:02.527 --> 38:25.118
the last, first and last Marine officer to ever 
hold that job because the military, the

38:02.527 --> 38:25.118
government, after I left there, went from the 
military government to the Samoan Defense Area

38:02.527 --> 38:25.118
back to the Navy, and from the Navy it went to the 
Department of the Interior, which is down there

38:02.527 --> 38:25.118
now. How'd you like that duty? I didn't like the 
duty. Why not? Because it was too... I had... I had

38:32.024 --> 38:34.147
every ship that came in there. I forgot that. Every 
ship that came in there, the skipper had to report

38:35.889 --> 38:38.832
to me. And if he was having any difficulties with 
the crew, I had power from Admiral Hawes to take him

38:39.413 --> 38:52.509
off and try him or send him back on his own 
transportation back to the United States and take

38:39.413 --> 38:52.509
him off the ship. That was some of my jobs. I had a lot 
of jobs to do. Did you ever have to do that with any

38:56.735 --> 38:58.537
captain? I did that with two or three people. I got a 
file of letters where lawyers wrote me after I went

39:01.437 --> 39:09.509
on inactive duty trying to straight them up and get 
their money back, but that didn't mean anything to

39:01.437 --> 39:09.509
me. I catch them stealing or selling whiskey on the 
beach, anything like that, and they brought them

39:10.811 --> 39:16.179
in. The skipper would come with the complaint and 
bring the defendant there, and then I'd take him

39:16.779 --> 39:23.489
from there.

39:27.836 --> 39:28.296
That was it. But I...

39:37.820 --> 39:39.041
It was a hell of a job. Another thing. Wait a minute. 
One of the things I had, I had a leper calling. I

39:43.946 --> 39:44.647
forgot that. Oh, you really? Give me a... Where's 
that damn thing? I forgot. Right here. That right

39:50.112 --> 39:50.713
there? No, I don't want that. You

39:53.496 --> 40:00.983
want a pen? Leper calling up on the side of the 
mountain. And I also ran the nut house. Crazy

40:06.228 --> 40:06.949
house.

40:12.025 --> 40:13.227
I had a feeder running that. One day he let a damn 
crazy guy get in there and drown. And he come

40:17.072 --> 40:21.218
telling me, I said, I just warned you last week. The 
ship was very well out of the water, and his name was

40:22.980 --> 40:27.226
Pai Tata. And he hit one of them natives who had a 
fake sardine can for a number. And he hit him and

40:35.277 --> 40:38.742
knocked him all down the ladder, and he hit the 
other guy. Every step on them buses, they had wide

40:38.958 --> 40:41.181
open. I had to relieve him of that, so I sent him over 
to the nut house, and next week he come over, he done

40:41.782 --> 40:48.812
drowned one of those poor crazy people. Oh, 
Christ. Well, who was your commanding general

40:51.516 --> 40:54.880
then? Was there a general in charge? There he is 
right there, General Henry L. Lawson. Lawson?

41:01.109 --> 41:01.650
That's right. Okay. He married. And so you were his 
assistant, more or less. No, this was back in his

41:07.221 --> 41:10.404
assistant. I was his provost and lieutenant 
general. He was the military governor. Okay, he

41:14.248 --> 41:15.710
was the military governor. This was back in Guam 
where I got the Legion of Merit.

